WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.870 --> 00:00:06.538
<i>♪♪</i>

2
00:00:12.513 --> 00:00:16.181
<i>And I've seen the promised land.</i>

3
00:00:16.250 --> 00:00:20.301
<i>In the beginning. God created
the heaven and the earth.</i>

4
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:24.355
<i>For those to whom much
is given. much is required.</i>

5
00:00:24.424 --> 00:00:27.008
<i>Thou shalt love thy
neighbor as thyself.</i>

6
00:00:27.077 --> 00:00:30.912
<i>Seek. and ye shall find.
Ask. and it shall be given.</i>

7
00:00:30.981 --> 00:00:35.700
<i>As the will of God is in
heaven. even so let it be.</i>

8
00:00:35.769 --> 00:00:38.604
<i>God is our refuge and strength.</i>

9
00:00:38.672 --> 00:00:42.423
<i>The most powerful
story of all time...</i>

10
00:00:42.492 --> 00:00:45.610
<i>continues to shape our world.</i>

11
00:00:45.679 --> 00:00:47.613
<i>It's the foundation
of our governments.</i>

12
00:00:48.716 --> 00:00:51.916
<i>the blueprint for our laws.</i>

13
00:00:51.985 --> 00:00:55.186
<i>a sacred guide
for life's journey.</i>

14
00:00:56.357 --> 00:00:58.790
<i>This is the Bible.</i>

15
00:01:03.029 --> 00:01:06.247
God warned me. He
told me to build a boat.

16
00:01:07.501 --> 00:01:10.369
<i>God has spoken to me.</i>

17
00:01:10.437 --> 00:01:12.470
<i>He will lead us to a new home.</i>

18
00:01:12.539 --> 00:01:16.524
<i>He has promised descendants
as numerous as the stars.</i>

19
00:01:19.129 --> 00:01:20.812
- <i>Who are you?</i>
- My name is Moses.

20
00:01:20.881 --> 00:01:24.098
<i>God has sent me to set you free.</i>

21
00:01:24.167 --> 00:01:29.171
<i>The Lord brought us out from
Egypt. promised us this land.</i>

22
00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:31.139
Soon it will be ours!

23
00:01:32.159 --> 00:01:34.454
Jerusalem. Our new home.

24
00:01:34.478 --> 00:01:37.796
David. you have forged
God's nation on Earth.

25
00:01:40.467 --> 00:01:43.218
<i>A nation and a
people find faith...</i>

26
00:01:43.286 --> 00:01:45.304
<i>in an all-powerful Creator.</i>

27
00:01:45.372 --> 00:01:47.823
God is with me!

28
00:01:49.543 --> 00:01:53.629
<i>Their story helps
define who we are...</i>

29
00:01:55.382 --> 00:01:57.732
<i>the choices we
make. how we live.</i>

30
00:01:58.885 --> 00:02:00.902
<i>how we love.</i>

31
00:02:00.971 --> 00:02:04.405
<i>how we struggle and overcome.</i>

32
00:02:04.474 --> 00:02:08.343
<i>Who created the
earth. the sea. the sky?</i>

33
00:02:08.412 --> 00:02:10.278
<i>Who created you?</i>

34
00:02:10.347 --> 00:02:11.746
Lord!

35
00:02:17.037 --> 00:02:19.254
<i>We give this city to the Lord!</i>

36
00:02:19.322 --> 00:02:21.256
Jericho is ours!

37
00:02:21.324 --> 00:02:25.027
<i>Whatever's left of
Jerusalem. help yourselves.</i>

38
00:02:25.095 --> 00:02:28.015
It's a trap for all of
us. They want us dead.

39
00:02:29.499 --> 00:02:33.769
<i>God is bringing
disaster from Babylon!</i>

40
00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:41.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

41
00:02:42.045 --> 00:02:47.115
Lady. I believe your son is
the promised king of his people.

42
00:02:47.184 --> 00:02:49.984
What is his name?

43
00:02:50.053 --> 00:02:51.553
Jesus.

44
00:02:53.189 --> 00:02:55.173
His name is Jesus.

45
00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:01.679
<i>You said there was trouble.</i>

46
00:03:01.748 --> 00:03:05.016
The people are flocking to this wild
man. John. They think he's a prophet.

47
00:03:05.085 --> 00:03:06.835
Some even call him the messiah.

48
00:03:06.903 --> 00:03:10.638
<i>There is one to come
who will baptize with fire.</i>

49
00:03:10.707 --> 00:03:13.667
I am just a voice in the wilderness.
preparing the way for the...

50
00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:18.697
Lord. what are we going to do?

51
00:03:18.765 --> 00:03:20.698
Change the world.

52
00:03:21.484 --> 00:03:23.802
Mary! He's here!

53
00:03:23.871 --> 00:03:25.804
Who? Jesus!

54
00:03:25.873 --> 00:03:27.873
He's back at last!

55
00:03:27.942 --> 00:03:31.109
<i>Blessed are the poor. for
theirs is the kingdom of heaven.</i>

56
00:03:31.177 --> 00:03:35.496
<i>Blessed are the meek. for
they shall inherit the earth.</i>

57
00:03:35.565 --> 00:03:40.602
What are you saying... that you are the
messiah. the chosen one sent by God?

58
00:03:40.671 --> 00:03:42.621
It has begun.

59
00:03:42.673 --> 00:03:46.591
Your hunger for righteousness.
it will be filled through me.

60
00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:49.260
<i>5.000 came to see him. 5.000.</i>

61
00:03:49.329 --> 00:03:53.765
<i>Your king comes to
you riding on a donkey.</i>

62
00:03:53.834 --> 00:03:56.584
<i>There is something
unusual about him.</i>

63
00:03:56.653 --> 00:04:00.105
There is nothing unusual about him
apart from his ability to cause havoc.

64
00:04:00.174 --> 00:04:03.141
<i>If the disturbances that took
place today are repeated.</i>

65
00:04:03.210 --> 00:04:05.626
I will crush any rebellion.

66
00:04:33.456 --> 00:04:35.423
<i>In the beginning.</i>

67
00:04:35.491 --> 00:04:39.928
<i>God created the
heavens and the earth.</i>

68
00:04:41.098 --> 00:04:43.031
<i>And God said.</i>

69
00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:45.200
<i>"Let there be light!"</i>

70
00:04:48.739 --> 00:04:51.890
<i>And there was light.</i>

71
00:04:59.332 --> 00:05:05.871
<i>Then God separated
the water and the sky.</i>

72
00:05:05.939 --> 00:05:09.074
<i>He formed the seas...</i>

73
00:05:09.143 --> 00:05:10.876
<i>and the land.</i>

74
00:05:18.485 --> 00:05:21.519
<i>Then he covered the land...</i>

75
00:05:21.588 --> 00:05:23.871
<i>with trees...</i>

76
00:05:25.091 --> 00:05:26.774
<i>and plants.</i>

77
00:05:37.037 --> 00:05:39.037
<i>Then he filled the world...</i>

78
00:05:40.106 --> 00:05:41.907
<i>with all the
creatures of the sea...</i>

79
00:05:48.564 --> 00:05:50.815
<i>of the air...</i>

80
00:05:55.154 --> 00:05:57.839
<i>and all the creatures
of the ground.</i>

81
00:06:05.982 --> 00:06:07.649
<i>And then...</i>

82
00:06:07.717 --> 00:06:10.702
<i>he made us...</i>

83
00:06:15.742 --> 00:06:18.360
<i>to live in paradise.</i>

84
00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:24.332
<i>until Adam and Eve
disobeyed God...</i>

85
00:06:26.135 --> 00:06:28.736
<i>and ate the forbidden fruit.</i>

86
00:06:34.928 --> 00:06:37.028
<i>And with one choice...</i>

87
00:06:37.097 --> 00:06:40.014
<i>they learned both good...</i>

88
00:06:41.351 --> 00:06:42.867
<i>and evil.</i>

89
00:06:44.471 --> 00:06:48.389
<i>Since then. since
Cain killed Abel.</i>

90
00:06:48.458 --> 00:06:52.293
<i>God has seen too much
evil in human hearts.</i>

91
00:07:09.329 --> 00:07:11.879
Wrong choices. Wrong decisions.

92
00:07:11.948 --> 00:07:15.282
That's why this...

93
00:07:15.351 --> 00:07:16.868
is happening.

94
00:07:18.672 --> 00:07:23.474
<i>Our Creator decided
to cleanse the earth.</i>

95
00:07:27.347 --> 00:07:31.482
God warned me. He
told me to build a boat.

96
00:07:36.306 --> 00:07:41.042
A boat to save our
family and all the animals.

97
00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:45.997
<i>Every other living creature...</i>

98
00:07:47.868 --> 00:07:50.251
<i>would die.</i>

99
00:08:09.856 --> 00:08:12.657
And on the seventh day.

100
00:08:12.726 --> 00:08:16.027
God... rested.

101
00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:02.774
<i>After the flood waters
engulfed the world.</i>

102
00:09:02.842 --> 00:09:06.544
<i>the Bible describes a new
beginning for Noah's descendants...</i>

103
00:09:06.613 --> 00:09:09.747
<i>and a chance to
restore the relationship...</i>

104
00:09:09.816 --> 00:09:12.183
<i>between God and humanity.</i>

105
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:18.957
<i>A new faith in an all-powerful
Creator is being born.</i>

106
00:09:24.447 --> 00:09:27.615
<i>But before billions
can believe in him.</i>

107
00:09:27.684 --> 00:09:29.884
<i>one man must hear God's voice...</i>

108
00:09:29.952 --> 00:09:33.087
<i>and have the faith to follow.</i>

109
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:46.367
<i>Abraham. leave your home...</i>

110
00:09:46.436 --> 00:09:49.803
<i>and go to the land I will
give to you and your offspring.</i>

111
00:09:53.143 --> 00:09:55.176
<i>I will bless you.</i>

112
00:09:55.245 --> 00:09:57.662
<i>I will make you a
father of many nations.</i>

113
00:09:58.731 --> 00:10:02.033
<i>with descendants as
numerous as the stars.</i>

114
00:10:04.805 --> 00:10:06.938
<i>All the peoples on earth...</i>

115
00:10:07.007 --> 00:10:09.490
<i>will be blessed through you.</i>

116
00:10:09.559 --> 00:10:11.726
Wait for me!

117
00:10:15.799 --> 00:10:19.317
Sarah. God has spoken to me.

118
00:10:20.303 --> 00:10:22.403
Come with me.

119
00:10:26.225 --> 00:10:29.260
Lot. my nephew. walk with us.

120
00:10:29.329 --> 00:10:30.978
Abraham?

121
00:10:32.332 --> 00:10:35.399
He will lead us to a new home.

122
00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:39.004
But... we have a
home. a good home.

123
00:10:39.072 --> 00:10:42.874
Away from the
city to a new land...

124
00:10:42.943 --> 00:10:44.308
for our children.

125
00:10:44.377 --> 00:10:48.079
But you have no children.
You can never have children.

126
00:10:48.148 --> 00:10:49.580
But we<i> will.</i>

127
00:10:49.649 --> 00:10:52.700
He has promised descendants
as numerous as the stars.

128
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:03.327
He spoke to me. He promised.

129
00:11:04.414 --> 00:11:07.215
Sarah. believe me.

130
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.336
Believe me.

131
00:11:22.248 --> 00:11:23.715
And. Lot.

132
00:11:23.783 --> 00:11:26.317
you are with me?

133
00:11:26.386 --> 00:11:29.304
He will lead us to
a land of wonder.

134
00:11:29.372 --> 00:11:30.855
No.

135
00:11:31.842 --> 00:11:34.008
No.

136
00:11:47.757 --> 00:11:49.757
Such wonder!

137
00:12:01.788 --> 00:12:05.039
<i>Driven by the belief that
he will father a great nation.</i>

138
00:12:05.108 --> 00:12:10.428
<i>Abraham leads his small tribe to
the land promised to him by God.</i>

139
00:12:25.178 --> 00:12:28.129
What else can I do? All
the other land is taken.

140
00:12:28.197 --> 00:12:32.066
No! You can't have mine!

141
00:12:36.138 --> 00:12:38.423
Now! Now!

142
00:12:38.492 --> 00:12:40.224
Stop! Come away!

143
00:12:42.144 --> 00:12:45.362
This can't go on. You've got to
tell Abraham what we decided.

144
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:46.780
What's going on?

145
00:12:46.849 --> 00:12:50.317
His men are trying
to take our pasture.

146
00:12:50.386 --> 00:12:52.803
God gave us this land to share.

147
00:12:52.872 --> 00:12:55.656
Then he should have
given us more of it.

148
00:12:55.725 --> 00:12:57.308
Tell him.

149
00:12:58.911 --> 00:13:02.480
Abraham. there just isn't enough
land. There are too many of us.

150
00:13:02.549 --> 00:13:04.748
The Lord will
provide. Have faith.

151
00:13:04.817 --> 00:13:08.097
In a god we cannot see?

152
00:13:09.438 --> 00:13:12.206
It's time we go
our separate ways.

153
00:13:12.275 --> 00:13:15.109
No. No. we must stay together.

154
00:13:15.178 --> 00:13:17.155
Stay and starve?

155
00:13:17.179 --> 00:13:20.499
Stay and watch our men kill
each other over a blade of grass?

156
00:13:24.971 --> 00:13:27.038
Uncle.

157
00:13:27.107 --> 00:13:28.655
we're leaving.

158
00:13:33.146 --> 00:13:34.846
Very well.

159
00:13:36.115 --> 00:13:38.115
Where do you want to go?

160
00:13:38.184 --> 00:13:41.052
To the greener pastures
closer to Sodom.

161
00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:43.370
Sodom?

162
00:13:49.045 --> 00:13:51.129
Take care.

163
00:13:51.198 --> 00:13:54.181
<i>With no children of his own.</i>

164
00:13:54.251 --> 00:13:59.287
<i>Abraham's nephew Lot is the
closest thing he has to a son.</i>

165
00:14:02.825 --> 00:14:05.393
How can I lead a people...

166
00:14:07.897 --> 00:14:11.365
when I can't even
lead my own family?

167
00:14:42.148 --> 00:14:44.115
Quickly! Help him!

168
00:14:44.184 --> 00:14:47.251
It's one of Lot's
men! It's Lemuel.

169
00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:50.321
Hurry! Somebody help him!

170
00:14:52.959 --> 00:14:55.142
Here. Lean on me.

171
00:14:55.211 --> 00:14:57.979
What happened? We
didn't stand a chance.

172
00:14:58.047 --> 00:15:00.314
There were so many of them.

173
00:15:00.383 --> 00:15:02.316
And Lot? Alive.

174
00:15:02.385 --> 00:15:04.986
- But taken prisoner.
- Help him.

175
00:15:05.054 --> 00:15:08.906
Here. Take my hand. Lean on me.

176
00:15:08.975 --> 00:15:10.719
That's better.

177
00:15:10.743 --> 00:15:12.409
Tend to him.

178
00:15:20.653 --> 00:15:22.587
We have some trained men.

179
00:15:22.655 --> 00:15:25.256
Abraham. you are not soldiers.

180
00:15:25.325 --> 00:15:29.727
I told them to trust in God. I made
Lot come with us. And then they left us.

181
00:15:29.795 --> 00:15:33.797
They had their pick of the land. It
was their choice. They are family.

182
00:15:36.002 --> 00:15:38.002
We have to help them.

183
00:15:40.806 --> 00:15:43.207
God will take care of us.

184
00:16:20.764 --> 00:16:24.348
♪♪

185
00:16:33.075 --> 00:16:36.027
♪♪

186
00:16:40.116 --> 00:16:42.567
What about this one. eh?

187
00:16:42.635 --> 00:16:44.851
Leave her alone there!

188
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:49.123
Let her go!

189
00:16:53.279 --> 00:16:54.412
Leave her alone!

190
00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:04.388
Trust in God!

191
00:17:47.783 --> 00:17:50.450
Are you all right?

192
00:18:00.997 --> 00:18:03.117
Lot.

193
00:18:05.050 --> 00:18:07.318
Oh. Lot.

194
00:18:12.558 --> 00:18:16.660
So few of us against so many.

195
00:18:18.498 --> 00:18:20.548
God is with us.

196
00:18:20.616 --> 00:18:22.166
Abraham.

197
00:18:22.235 --> 00:18:24.502
We're carrying on to Sodom.

198
00:18:31.644 --> 00:18:35.596
Lot. we must stay together.

199
00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:38.165
No.

200
00:18:40.669 --> 00:18:42.419
No. Uncle.

201
00:18:45.008 --> 00:18:46.908
We can't.

202
00:18:48.177 --> 00:18:50.177
We have to carry on.

203
00:18:56.852 --> 00:18:58.385
Let's go.

204
00:19:26.482 --> 00:19:27.982
Abraham.

205
00:19:29.151 --> 00:19:30.617
Come inside.

206
00:19:30.686 --> 00:19:32.185
The stars.

207
00:19:34.123 --> 00:19:36.390
Abraham? The stars.

208
00:19:36.459 --> 00:19:38.492
All of them.

209
00:19:38.561 --> 00:19:40.105
Count them. Abraham.

210
00:19:40.129 --> 00:19:42.680
Count them. Count them.

211
00:19:46.218 --> 00:19:48.469
Our Creator... Shh.

212
00:19:48.537 --> 00:19:51.054
Who made the stars.

213
00:19:51.123 --> 00:19:53.090
will give us as
many descendants...

214
00:19:53.159 --> 00:19:54.659
Shh. shh. shh.

215
00:19:54.727 --> 00:19:57.161
To populate our land.

216
00:19:59.048 --> 00:20:01.248
He has promised.

217
00:20:01.317 --> 00:20:03.128
You<i> will</i> have a child. I won't.

218
00:20:03.152 --> 00:20:04.986
You<i> will!</i> I won't!

219
00:20:05.655 --> 00:20:07.287
I can't.

220
00:20:09.125 --> 00:20:11.425
It's too late for me.

221
00:20:16.282 --> 00:20:18.449
For you. there's still a chance.

222
00:20:25.491 --> 00:20:27.023
Her.

223
00:20:29.963 --> 00:20:33.297
Hagar. the servant girl.

224
00:20:39.272 --> 00:20:41.205
No.

225
00:20:41.274 --> 00:20:43.740
No. no. no.

226
00:20:43.809 --> 00:20:45.309
No.

227
00:20:52.801 --> 00:20:54.634
Yes.

228
00:22:18.488 --> 00:22:20.688
Hold it steady. Ishmael.

229
00:22:30.133 --> 00:22:33.133
Sarah. did you see that?

230
00:22:33.202 --> 00:22:35.686
Did you see that? Oh. my boy!

231
00:22:35.755 --> 00:22:37.421
My boy!

232
00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:43.460
"My boy."

233
00:22:45.564 --> 00:22:47.064
<i>Your</i> boy.

234
00:22:50.803 --> 00:22:52.669
Go with your mother.

235
00:23:13.860 --> 00:23:15.342
<i>Abraham.</i>

236
00:23:54.149 --> 00:23:56.900
Welcome. Lord.

237
00:24:01.040 --> 00:24:02.939
Please...

238
00:24:03.008 --> 00:24:05.175
join me.

239
00:24:05.244 --> 00:24:07.289
Bring water. Prepare
food for our visitors.

240
00:24:07.313 --> 00:24:08.812
Yes. master.

241
00:24:25.181 --> 00:24:27.848
Have you traveled far?

242
00:24:27.916 --> 00:24:29.366
Yes.

243
00:24:29.435 --> 00:24:31.502
A long way.

244
00:24:33.639 --> 00:24:37.624
Abraham. where is your wife?

245
00:24:41.263 --> 00:24:43.280
In there.

246
00:24:45.318 --> 00:24:48.501
Next year. Sarah
will have a son.

247
00:24:57.797 --> 00:24:59.917
Why do you laugh?

248
00:25:05.571 --> 00:25:08.011
But I did not laugh. You did.

249
00:25:09.458 --> 00:25:11.436
And when you have a son.

250
00:25:11.460 --> 00:25:14.812
you will name him Isaac.

251
00:25:15.631 --> 00:25:18.565
which means "laughter."

252
00:25:26.775 --> 00:25:29.142
Thank you for your hospitality.

253
00:25:29.211 --> 00:25:30.711
We must go.

254
00:25:30.779 --> 00:25:32.863
Can I help you on your way?

255
00:25:34.249 --> 00:25:36.016
Where are you going?

256
00:25:38.154 --> 00:25:40.170
To decide the fate of Sodom.

257
00:25:46.095 --> 00:25:49.596
♪♪

258
00:25:51.733 --> 00:25:53.733
Get out of here!

259
00:26:06.015 --> 00:26:08.559
Sodom has become corrupt.

260
00:26:08.583 --> 00:26:10.350
a city of sin.

261
00:26:13.839 --> 00:26:16.406
<i>But my nephew Lot lives there.</i>

262
00:26:16.475 --> 00:26:18.242
<i>He has a family.</i>

263
00:26:21.229 --> 00:26:24.381
<i>The outcry against
Sodom is great.</i>

264
00:26:25.167 --> 00:26:28.535
Its sins are very grave.

265
00:26:32.041 --> 00:26:34.041
You're going to destroy it.

266
00:26:34.109 --> 00:26:36.776
The whole city?

267
00:26:48.991 --> 00:26:51.508
<i>You are a just God.</i>

268
00:26:51.577 --> 00:26:55.111
Will you destroy the good men...

269
00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:57.464
- Inside.
- <i>along with the evil ones?</i>

270
00:26:59.368 --> 00:27:02.152
Please! Help!

271
00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:04.087
Help us!

272
00:27:04.156 --> 00:27:05.522
Help!

273
00:27:06.925 --> 00:27:10.527
What if there were 50
good people in Sodom?

274
00:27:10.595 --> 00:27:14.681
Will they suffer the
same fate as the wicked?

275
00:27:14.750 --> 00:27:16.744
Please help us!

276
00:27:16.768 --> 00:27:18.479
<i>We will test them.</i>

277
00:27:18.503 --> 00:27:22.089
If my angels find 50
righteous people in Sodom.

278
00:27:23.258 --> 00:27:25.698
<i>I will spare the whole city.</i>

279
00:27:28.213 --> 00:27:30.330
Please. Help us.

280
00:27:30.399 --> 00:27:33.027
They went this way! Help us.

281
00:27:33.051 --> 00:27:36.770
Or fewer. Thirty. Twenty.

282
00:27:36.839 --> 00:27:39.689
<i>You would not
destroy them. surely.</i>

283
00:27:39.758 --> 00:27:42.186
Please. There! Down there!

284
00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:43.810
Help us!

285
00:27:43.879 --> 00:27:45.896
Please. This way.

286
00:27:45.965 --> 00:27:49.282
What if there were 10
righteous men in Sodom?

287
00:27:50.452 --> 00:27:52.185
<i>Would you not save them?</i>

288
00:27:52.254 --> 00:27:55.556
Lot. what are you doing?
Who are these people?

289
00:27:55.624 --> 00:27:57.774
They need our help.

290
00:27:59.361 --> 00:28:01.795
I'll do what I can for you.

291
00:28:01.863 --> 00:28:04.848
<i>Even if I find only 10.</i>

292
00:28:04.917 --> 00:28:06.945
I will save the whole city.

293
00:28:06.969 --> 00:28:08.763
This way! Where can they be?

294
00:28:08.787 --> 00:28:11.187
- Show yourselves!
- Show yourself!

295
00:28:11.256 --> 00:28:13.540
Mother.

296
00:28:13.609 --> 00:28:15.529
Shh!

297
00:28:20.149 --> 00:28:22.315
What's that?

298
00:28:22.384 --> 00:28:24.701
They're behind the
door! Over there!

299
00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:27.921
- Open the door! Open the door!
- What do they want?

300
00:28:27.989 --> 00:28:30.674
- Lot!
- Give us the strangers!

301
00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:36.196
Bring them out!

302
00:28:36.264 --> 00:28:38.559
They are guests in
my house. Let us pass!

303
00:28:38.583 --> 00:28:40.700
Let them be! Or
we'll take you too!

304
00:28:40.769 --> 00:28:42.702
Show yourselves!

305
00:28:42.771 --> 00:28:45.672
Send them out!

306
00:28:57.519 --> 00:28:59.919
Step aside.

307
00:29:23.745 --> 00:29:26.413
- We must go.
- I can't see!

308
00:29:26.481 --> 00:29:28.381
Come on!

309
00:29:29.802 --> 00:29:32.368
For Abraham's sake.
the Lord is saving you.

310
00:29:32.437 --> 00:29:34.220
Keep moving. That's it.

311
00:29:35.841 --> 00:29:37.323
Wait.

312
00:29:38.460 --> 00:29:40.126
There they are!

313
00:30:14.112 --> 00:30:16.046
Let's go.

314
00:30:37.569 --> 00:30:40.887
Have faith. Abraham.

315
00:31:25.750 --> 00:31:28.669
You are safe now.

316
00:31:28.737 --> 00:31:32.238
You must get away. The
city is being punished.

317
00:31:33.825 --> 00:31:35.993
Keep moving. Come on!

318
00:31:37.278 --> 00:31:40.614
Keep moving. Keep
moving. Come on.

319
00:31:40.683 --> 00:31:42.810
Do not look back
at the city of sin!

320
00:31:42.834 --> 00:31:45.285
Believe in God.

321
00:31:45.353 --> 00:31:47.787
Do not look back!

322
00:31:47.856 --> 00:31:50.690
Lot.

323
00:32:05.007 --> 00:32:06.856
Come on!

324
00:32:06.925 --> 00:32:08.725
Don't look back!

325
00:32:11.697 --> 00:32:13.196
No!

326
00:32:23.425 --> 00:32:26.393
<i>Lot's wife is turned
into a pillar of salt...</i>

327
00:32:26.461 --> 00:32:27.961
<i>for disobeying God.</i>

328
00:32:29.715 --> 00:32:33.016
<i>Lot and his daughters
flee to the mountains.</i>

329
00:32:33.085 --> 00:32:35.801
<i>never to see Abraham again.</i>

330
00:32:52.487 --> 00:32:54.421
How is she?

331
00:32:54.489 --> 00:32:56.389
How is she?

332
00:33:35.764 --> 00:33:38.297
Oh. Oh.

333
00:33:39.501 --> 00:33:42.002
Oh!

334
00:33:52.464 --> 00:33:55.232
A boy.

335
00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:57.345
Isaac.

336
00:33:57.369 --> 00:33:59.136
As he promised.

337
00:34:23.511 --> 00:34:27.814
♪♪

338
00:34:31.219 --> 00:34:32.585
Ooh!

339
00:34:37.459 --> 00:34:39.125
Your bread.

340
00:34:41.963 --> 00:34:44.123
Eat your food. Ishmael.

341
00:34:46.134 --> 00:34:47.945
Ishmael.

342
00:34:47.969 --> 00:34:49.647
This way! Come on!

343
00:34:49.671 --> 00:34:52.304
- I am!
- Hurry! Hurry!

344
00:34:53.592 --> 00:34:55.692
Ah.

345
00:34:55.761 --> 00:34:58.528
Oh. good.

346
00:35:19.318 --> 00:35:21.618
Sarah?

347
00:35:22.887 --> 00:35:24.570
What's the matter?

348
00:35:24.639 --> 00:35:28.941
That woman thinks her boy is going to
inherit what rightfully belongs to Isaac.

349
00:35:29.010 --> 00:35:30.510
What do you mean?

350
00:35:34.166 --> 00:35:36.982
Who is to be the first of
all our tribe. Abraham...

351
00:35:37.051 --> 00:35:40.903
The first star of all those
stars in the heavens?

352
00:35:43.074 --> 00:35:44.674
<i>Our</i> son...

353
00:35:46.044 --> 00:35:47.359
or hers?

354
00:35:47.428 --> 00:35:49.128
Sarah. I... Abraham.

355
00:35:49.197 --> 00:35:51.197
Abraham!

356
00:35:51.266 --> 00:35:52.799
You decide!

357
00:35:55.771 --> 00:35:57.303
Mama.

358
00:35:58.940 --> 00:36:01.207
Or let God decide.

359
00:36:44.936 --> 00:36:46.569
Be brave.

360
00:36:55.430 --> 00:36:59.382
<i>Assured by God
that they will survive.</i>

361
00:36:59.450 --> 00:37:04.254
<i>Abraham sends Hagar and
Ishmael into the wilderness.</i>

362
00:37:16.534 --> 00:37:18.601
Good-bye. Ishmael.

363
00:37:20.021 --> 00:37:21.638
Oh. my boy.

364
00:37:22.741 --> 00:37:24.808
My boy.

365
00:37:24.876 --> 00:37:26.576
When you grow up.

366
00:37:26.645 --> 00:37:29.628
God will bless you
with many children.

367
00:38:03.164 --> 00:38:05.098
Mmm.

368
00:38:05.166 --> 00:38:08.100
Let me make you
some breakfast. Isaac.

369
00:38:08.169 --> 00:38:09.668
<i>After years of struggle.</i>

370
00:38:09.737 --> 00:38:13.857
<i>Abraham has learned
that to be chosen by God...</i>

371
00:38:13.925 --> 00:38:17.460
<i>is a blessing and a test.</i>

372
00:38:17.529 --> 00:38:19.529
<i>He must prove his faith...</i>

373
00:38:19.598 --> 00:38:22.632
<i>again and again.</i>

374
00:38:41.353 --> 00:38:42.969
A sacrifice.

375
00:38:47.075 --> 00:38:48.608
No.

376
00:38:50.078 --> 00:38:52.295
No.

377
00:38:52.364 --> 00:38:55.481
Have I not shown
you enough faith?

378
00:39:03.291 --> 00:39:05.157
Isaac.

379
00:39:16.671 --> 00:39:18.304
Eat up.

380
00:39:18.373 --> 00:39:22.292
When you have children of your own.
you'll want them to grow up as big and...

381
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.227
Abraham?

382
00:39:27.499 --> 00:39:29.298
What's the matter?

383
00:39:34.072 --> 00:39:36.339
God wants a sacrifice.

384
00:39:38.343 --> 00:39:41.093
My boy. come with me.

385
00:40:15.263 --> 00:40:18.030
Hello.

386
00:41:06.080 --> 00:41:08.864
Father. we have the firewood.

387
00:41:08.933 --> 00:41:11.266
But where's the lamb?

388
00:41:17.408 --> 00:41:21.477
The Lord will provide
a sacrifice. my son.

389
00:41:33.575 --> 00:41:35.141
Did Abraham take a lamb?

390
00:41:35.209 --> 00:41:38.244
No. mistress.

391
00:41:57.482 --> 00:41:59.482
Bring the wood.

392
00:42:25.844 --> 00:42:27.710
Father?

393
00:42:27.779 --> 00:42:29.362
What are you doing?

394
00:42:32.984 --> 00:42:35.919
You're hurting me. Father.

395
00:42:35.987 --> 00:42:40.272
Isaac. we must trust in God.

396
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:02.187
No. Please.

397
00:43:05.616 --> 00:43:07.232
No.

398
00:43:13.374 --> 00:43:14.940
Please.

399
00:43:15.009 --> 00:43:17.276
Please.

400
00:43:17.345 --> 00:43:19.746
Please. Father.

401
00:43:20.682 --> 00:43:22.682
Forgive me.

402
00:43:25.770 --> 00:43:27.770
Please.

403
00:43:44.005 --> 00:43:46.422
<i>Abraham!</i>

404
00:43:58.436 --> 00:44:00.603
A sacrifice.

405
00:44:02.807 --> 00:44:06.008
Oh. my boy. my boy. my boy.

406
00:44:38.743 --> 00:44:42.561
No. No.

407
00:44:45.800 --> 00:44:47.884
Isaac!

408
00:45:04.469 --> 00:45:06.569
Mother!

409
00:45:10.257 --> 00:45:13.492
<i>Abraham has passed
the ultimate test.</i>

410
00:45:13.561 --> 00:45:17.329
<i>He will become the
father of God's nation.</i>

411
00:45:20.234 --> 00:45:22.285
<i>Now it's up to Isaac.</i>

412
00:45:23.221 --> 00:45:26.155
<i>He will have a son called Jacob.</i>

413
00:45:26.224 --> 00:45:29.458
<i>God will rename him Israel.</i>

414
00:45:30.728 --> 00:45:34.663
<i>The promise of descendants
as numerous as the stars...</i>

415
00:45:34.732 --> 00:45:36.299
<i>is coming true.</i>

416
00:45:37.702 --> 00:45:42.438
<i>But famine forces the Israelites
far from the promised land...</i>

417
00:45:42.507 --> 00:45:44.356
<i>to Egypt.</i>

418
00:45:46.760 --> 00:45:50.196
<i>Here they are
enslaved by Pharaoh.</i>

419
00:45:50.264 --> 00:45:53.866
<i>Abraham and God
become a distant memory.</i>

420
00:45:54.935 --> 00:45:58.371
<i>all his people reduced
to beasts of burden.</i>

421
00:46:00.141 --> 00:46:01.874
<i>except one.</i>

422
00:46:02.576 --> 00:46:04.760
Moses.

423
00:46:04.829 --> 00:46:07.880
<i>Next time on</i> The Bible.

424
00:46:07.949 --> 00:46:10.043
- You're not
going to fight again.
- I can't refuse.

425
00:46:10.067 --> 00:46:11.934
He's Pharaoh's son.

426
00:46:12.003 --> 00:46:14.920
<i>Fight me! I order you!</i>

427
00:46:15.840 --> 00:46:17.323
Yaah!

428
00:46:17.392 --> 00:46:19.942
- You're not one of us.
- What's he talking about?

429
00:46:20.011 --> 00:46:22.128
<i>You were born a slave.</i>

430
00:46:23.630 --> 00:46:27.165
<i>- Your people</i>
<i>are out there. Moses.</i>
- No! Aaah!

431
00:46:27.234 --> 00:46:29.001
<i>- The Israelites.</i>
- Run!

432
00:46:30.054 --> 00:46:33.456
<i>Welcome to your new life. Moses!</i>

433
00:46:33.525 --> 00:46:36.058
<i>You are nothing now!</i>

434
00:46:37.996 --> 00:46:39.829
You are the God of Abraham.

435
00:46:39.898 --> 00:46:44.016
<i>I will do it. I will
set my people free.</i>

436
00:46:45.136 --> 00:46:47.152
<i>So much suffering.</i>

437
00:46:47.221 --> 00:46:49.288
Please!

438
00:46:49.356 --> 00:46:52.991
- <i>Who are you?</i>
- My name is Moses.

439
00:46:53.060 --> 00:46:54.877
Joshua.

440
00:46:54.946 --> 00:46:59.348
<i>God has sent me to set you free.</i>

441
00:46:59.416 --> 00:47:03.101
- Why are you here. Moses?
- Let my people go.

442
00:47:04.004 --> 00:47:06.939
Freedom? They
are free to choose.

443
00:47:07.007 --> 00:47:09.825
<i>Slavery or death!</i>

444
00:47:09.894 --> 00:47:14.213
All my life I have been Pharaoh's.
I will never be a slave again.

445
00:47:14.282 --> 00:47:17.633
Joshua. God is with us.

446
00:47:17.702 --> 00:47:19.819
<i>The Angel of Death is coming.</i>

447
00:47:22.957 --> 00:47:25.508
<i>Go! And leave my land!</i>

448
00:47:25.576 --> 00:47:27.877
And take your
wretched God with you!

449
00:47:40.974 --> 00:47:43.374
The Egyptians... they're here.

450
00:47:44.879 --> 00:47:47.479
Lord!

451
00:47:52.887 --> 00:47:55.171
Follow me!

452
00:47:57.758 --> 00:47:59.008
Bring me Moses!

453
00:48:16.360 --> 00:48:20.329
<i>♪♪</i>

453
00:48:21.305 --> 00:49:21.392
Do you want subtitles for any video?
